# {{ projectName }}

DARE-shaped MCP server (Rust, rmcp SDK). Default transport: **{{ defaultTransport }}**. BETA.

## Setup

```bash
cp .env.example .env
cargo build
cargo run
```

## Commands

- `cargo run` — start server (transport via --transport or MCP_TRANSPORT env)
- `cargo test` — tests
- `cargo clippy -- -D warnings` — lint
- `cargo audit` — RustSec advisory audit
- `npx @modelcontextprotocol/inspector cargo run` — MCP Inspector

## Tools (registered in src/server.rs)

| Name | Input | Output | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `echo` | `text: String` | `String` | Returns input verbatim. Smoke test. |

## Prompts

| Name | Args | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `summarize` | `text` | Summarize the input text. Placeholder. |

## Transports

Choose with `--transport stdio|sse|http` or `MCP_TRANSPORT`:

- `stdio` (default) — local agents. No port.
- `sse` — SSE-over-HTTP on MCP_PORT (default 3001), served by axum.
- `http` — Streamable HTTP on MCP_PORT, served by axum.

## Architecture

- `src/main.rs` — tokio entrypoint, parses args, dispatches transport.
- `src/server.rs` — builds the rmcp service with tools + prompts.
- `src/cli.rs` — clap arg parser + Transport enum + --list-tools.
- `src/transports/{stdio,sse,http}.rs` — one runner per transport.
- `src/tools/`, `src/prompts/` — pure functions, unit-tested.

## CLI inventory

`cargo run -- --json --list-tools` prints the tool registry as JSON (M-03).

## Note on beta status

`rmcp` is the official Rust MCP SDK but its API is pre-1.0. If a `cargo build`
fails after a dependency update, pin `rmcp` to a known-good version in Cargo.toml.

